    • Method Detail

      • gwtModule

        public HostPage.Builder gwtModule(java.lang.String value)
        Overrides the default value for gwtModule By default gwtModule is the string specified for the rename-to attribute of the module tag in the gwt.xml configuration file for the GWT module. This value appears in the host page as the src attribute of the <script> tag which references your GWT module. For example, <script type="text/javascript" src="gwtModule/gwtModule.nocache.js"></script>
        Parameters:
        value - Name of the GWT Module to be loaded by the host page
        Returns:
        Builder instance having value for gwtModule

      • hostPage

        public HostPage.Builder hostPage(java.lang.String value)
        Overrides the default value for hostPage which is an DAO.getDefaultPage().getPageName() Value must be a valid Page or Landing name as defined in the GAE data-store for Page and Landing objects having a revision value of 'current' or and empty string. In the case of value specified as an empty string, or a string which is not a valid name of an existing Page or Landing object, the default value for hostPage is used, i.e., the value specified for defaultPage in the Site configuration object, which is returned by the call DAO.getDefaultPage.getPageName().
        Parameters:
        value -
        Returns:
        Builder instance having a modified value for hostPage
